The paper discusses a machine learning approach to reduce false alarms in ICU monitoring systems, which involves processing multivariate time series data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Among these, cs.LG is the most likely category, as the paper focuses on developing a novel multitask network architecture for machine learning. The other categories are also relevant, as the paper discusses the application of machine learning to a critical care setting, which involves human-computer interaction and computational engineering.
